text.text: I had an amazing stay at Taragarh Palace with my family.Tucked away in the tranquil embrace of the mountains, my stay at Taragarh was like stepping into a fairytale. The aura of history enveloped me as I wandered through its halls, adorned with vintage decor and steeped in stories from times past. The staff treated me like family, ensuring every moment was filled with warmth and hospitality. Waking up to the majestic peaks outside my window was a dream come true, and each day brought new adventures, from scenic hikes to lush green tea garden was a quiet moments of reflection. Taragarh is more than a hotel; it's a sanctuary of serenity and charm.

Meals service are so dynamic and delicious. Cleaning of rooms are also Appreciable..I personally recommend visiters to spend your time here for relaxing from running life...Surely it will not waste of time, inspite it boost your energy level..i wish all my best wishes and definitely visit The Royal Taragarh palace in future...

text.text:
The staff was extremely impolite and unprofessional, dressed in sweatshirts and pajamas. The chicken served was cold, despite my request to warm it up, which the server forgot to serve again and the kitchen had already reheated. Despite being the only customers, they still managed to overlook our order. This seems to be a recurring issue, as evidenced by other reviews. Furthermore, they overcharged us compared to the menu prices, attributing it to a company-wide rate increase, which is unacceptable as their menu wasn’t updated.

Consequently, we will not be returning ever.

text.text:
Amazing experience. Rest house is very good and the best part is that the owner is very kind and helpful. They have arranged all the facilities to make our tour easy and memorable. Rest house is very close to market.
We really enjoyed our stay and loved that the traditional furnishings. The rooms are spacious and the bathroom was clean. They take care of your all needs and demand. In one line you would feel you are living in your own house not in any hotel or guest house. Food cooked is just fingerlicious.

I would recommend this as a nice authentic stay in Baijnath (H.P), and would say it's particularly great for families & couples.  Perfect place to have complete peace of mind. Would highly recommend to every one .

text.text: Highly recommended for a stay in Baijnath. The owner, Mr. Ashok Goswami is very polite and helpful just like the staff especially Ashu. They helped us to plan our 3 day itinerary and it was perfect. I went with my parents to find our long lost relatives and they helped us track them too. Apparently the town is very small and they all know each other. Food is amazing and does not burn a hole in your pocket. Thumbs up!
